What's the smallest positive integer that gives no Google hits?

What's the smallest positive integer that gives no Google hits? — Somewhere between 52 and 77 million, there exists a number that, when Googled, returns no results. However, should we ever find it, Google will probably index the webpage containing the article.

Enjoy your day.
